spec: socket_extra56
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "socket_extra55.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket/herror/gaierror/timeout __repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function'/'wrapper_descriptor'); SOCK_RAW.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__('SocketKind'); socket.socket TYPE __hash__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor')."
    - "socket_extra54.zspec.zsdl — covers herror/gaierror/timeout/gethostbyname/setdefaulttimeout __class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins'); herror/gaierror/timeout __init__.__class__.__name__/__module__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor'/'builtins')."
    - "socket_extra53.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket/herror/gaierror/timeout __dict__/__class__/__qualname__.__eq__('mappingproxy'); socket module __dict__/__class__.__name__/__qualname__.__eq__('mappingproxy')."
    - "socket_extra52.zspec.zsdl — covers AF_INET6/AF_UNIX __class__.__qualname__/__module__.__eq__ and __class__.__qualname__.__len__()==13."
    - "socket_extra51.zspec.zsdl — covers AF_INET/SOCK_STREAM/SOCK_DGRAM __class__.__module__.__eq__('socket') and __len__()==6; SOCK_DGRAM __class__.__qualname__.__eq__('SocketKind') and __len__()==10."
    - "socket_extra30.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.__all__.__len__()==238 and socket.__all__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('list') (as invariants); AF_INET/AF_INET6 __class__.__name__.__eq__('AddressFamily'); SOCK_STREAM/SOCK_DGRAM __class__.__name__.__eq__('SocketKind')."
    - "socket_extra2.zspec.zsdl — covers AF_INET/AF_INET6/AF_UNIX/__class__/__name__.__eq__('AddressFamily'); SOCK_STREAM/DGRAM/RAW/__class__/__name__.__eq__('SocketKind')."
  notes:
    - "This spec extends socket through socket_extra55; it does NOT duplicate invariants present in those files."
    - "Wave 223 theme: module __all__ content + __eq__.__class__.__name__ checks."
    - "Coverage gap 1: socket_extra30 covers socket.__all__.__len__()==238 and socket.__all__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('list') (as standalone invariants). No prior socket spec checks socket.__all__.__contains__ for specific member names. socket.__all__ is a list of 238 public names; checking __contains__ for key names (AF_INET, SOCK_STREAM, socket the class, herror, gaierror) confirms that the declared public API includes both enum constants and exception types. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__all__.__contains__('AF_INET') == True. 'AF_INET' is in socket.__all__; socket_extra30 checks __all__.__len__ and __class__.__name__ but NOT __contains__. No prior socket spec checks __all__.__contains__('AF_INET'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__all__.__contains__('SOCK_STREAM') == True. 'SOCK_STREAM' is in socket.__all__; no prior socket spec checks __all__.__contains__('SOCK_STREAM'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__all__.__contains__('socket') == True. 'socket' (the class name) is in socket.__all__; no prior socket spec checks __all__.__contains__('socket'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__all__.__contains__('herror') == True. 'herror' is in socket.__all__; no prior socket spec checks __all__.__contains__('herror'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__all__.__contains__('gaierror') == True. 'gaierror' is in socket.__all__; no prior socket spec checks __all__.__contains__('gaierror'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Coverage gap 2: No prior socket spec checks socket.socket.__eq__.__class__.__name__. socket_extra55 covers socket.socket.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function') and socket.socket.__hash__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor'). But no prior spec checks socket.socket.__eq__.__class__.__name__. socket.socket is a Python class defined in Lib/socket.py; it does not define __eq__ explicitly, so __eq__ is inherited from object as a wrapper_descriptor. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. socket.socket inherits __eq__ from object (a C type); the TYPE-level __eq__ is a wrapper_descriptor (C slot wrapper for tp_richcompare). socket_extra55 covers __repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function') and __hash__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') for socket.socket, but NOT __eq__.__class__.__name__. No prior socket spec checks socket.socket.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Coverage gap 3: No prior socket spec checks herror/gaierror/timeout __eq__.__class__.__name__. socket_extra55 covers herror/gaierror/timeout __repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor'). socket_extra54 covers __init__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') for herror/gaierror/timeout. But no prior spec checks __eq__.__class__.__name__ for these exception classes. herror, gaierror, and timeout are Python subclasses of OSError (ultimately BaseException, a C type); their __eq__ is inherited as a wrapper_descriptor. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.herror.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. herror inherits __eq__ from the exception hierarchy (ultimately BaseException, a C type); the TYPE-level __eq__ is a wrapper_descriptor. socket_extra55 covers herror.__repr__.__class__.__name__ but NOT herror.__eq__.__class__.__name__. No prior socket spec checks herror.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.gaierror.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. Same pattern as herror. No prior socket spec checks gaierror.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.timeout.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. Same pattern as herror/gaierror. No prior socket spec checks timeout.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Coverage gap 4: No prior socket spec checks __eq__.__class__.__name__ for AF_INET or SOCK_STREAM. socket_extra2 covers AF_INET/__class__/__name__.__eq__('AddressFamily') and SOCK_STREAM/__class__/__name__.__eq__('SocketKind') — the class of the enum member. socket_extra30 covers AF_INET/__class__/__name__.__eq__('AddressFamily') (the type axis). But no prior spec checks AF_INET.__eq__.__class__.__name__ or SOCK_STREAM.__eq__.__class__.__name__. AF_INET and SOCK_STREAM are IntEnum instances (not types); their __eq__ is a bound method-wrapper (the C slot for __eq__ bound to the specific instance). Instance-level __eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.AF_INET.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper'. AF_INET is an AddressFamily IntEnum instance; at the instance level, __eq__ is a bound method-wrapper (C slot wrapper bound to the specific instance). Distinct from the TYPE-level wrapper_descriptor: method-wrapper is the bound form. No prior socket spec checks AF_INET.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method-wrapper'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.SOCK_STREAM.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper'. SOCK_STREAM is a SocketKind IntEnum instance; same bound method-wrapper pattern as AF_INET. No prior socket spec checks SOCK_STREAM.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method-wrapper'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.__all__.__contains__ for key public names
#
# socket_extra30 covers socket.__all__.__len__()==238 and
# socket.__all__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('list') as standalone invariants.
# No prior socket spec checks socket.__all__.__contains__ for any specific name.
# socket.__all__ is a list of 238 names; checking membership confirms that
# the declared public API includes enum constants (AF_INET, SOCK_STREAM),
# the socket class, and exception types (herror, gaierror).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table socket_extra56.all_contains:
  description: "socket.__all__.__contains__('AF_INET'/'SOCK_STREAM'/'socket'/'herror'/'gaierror') — confirms key names in the declared public API list; socket_extra30 covers __all__.__len__()==238 and __class__.__name__.__eq__('list') but NOT __contains__; no prior socket spec checks __all__.__contains__ for any specific name"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: module_structure
  id_prefix: socketall56

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - [all_contains_AF_INET,      __all__.__contains__, ["AF_INET"],      true]
    - [all_contains_SOCK_STREAM,  __all__.__contains__, ["SOCK_STREAM"],  true]
    - [all_contains_socket,       __all__.__contains__, ["socket"],       true]
    - [all_contains_herror,       __all__.__contains__, ["herror"],       true]
    - [all_contains_gaierror,     __all__.__contains__, ["gaierror"],     true]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.socket TYPE __eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor')
#
# socket_extra55 covers socket.socket.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function')
# and socket.socket.__hash__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor').
# No prior socket spec checks socket.socket.__eq__.__class__.__name__.
# socket.socket does not define __eq__ explicitly; it inherits __eq__ from object
# as a wrapper_descriptor (C slot wrapper for tp_richcompare).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table socket_extra56.socket_eq_class_name:
  description: "socket.socket/__eq__/__class__/__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') — socket.socket inherits __eq__ from object as a wrapper_descriptor; socket_extra55 covers __repr__ and __hash__ class names for socket.socket but NOT __eq__; no prior socket spec checks socket.socket.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor')"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: type_structure
  id_prefix: socketall56

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - [socket_eq_class_name_eq, socket.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["wrapper_descriptor"], true]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.herror/gaierror/timeout TYPE __eq__.__class__.__name__
#
# socket_extra55 covers herror/gaierror/timeout __repr__.__class__.__name__
# (all 'wrapper_descriptor'). socket_extra54 covers __init__.__class__.__name__
# (all 'wrapper_descriptor'). But no prior spec checks __eq__.__class__.__name__
# for these exception classes. herror, gaierror, and timeout inherit __eq__
# from BaseException (a C type) as a wrapper_descriptor.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table socket_extra56.exceptions_eq_class_name:
  description: "socket.herror/gaierror/timeout/__eq__/__class__/__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') — exception classes inherit __eq__ from BaseException (C type) as a wrapper_descriptor; socket_extra55 covers __repr__ class name and socket_extra54 covers __init__ class name for these exceptions but neither checks __eq__.__class__.__name__; no prior socket spec checks __eq__.__class__.__name__ for herror, gaierror, or timeout"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: type_structure
  id_prefix: socketall56

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - [herror_eq_class_name_eq,  herror.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,  ["wrapper_descriptor"], true]
    - [gaierror_eq_class_name_eq, gaierror.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["wrapper_descriptor"], true]
    - [timeout_eq_class_name_eq,  timeout.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,  ["wrapper_descriptor"], true]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.AF_INET and SOCK_STREAM INSTANCE __eq__.__class__.__name__
#
# AF_INET (AddressFamily IntEnum) and SOCK_STREAM (SocketKind IntEnum) are
# instances (not types). At the instance level, __eq__ is a bound method-wrapper
# (the C slot wrapper bound to the specific instance), unlike the TYPE-level
# wrapper_descriptor. socket_extra2 covers AF_INET/__class__/__name__.__eq__ and
# socket_extra30 covers the same — both check the TYPE of the enum member, not
# the class of the instance's __eq__ attribute. No prior socket spec checks
# AF_INET.__eq__.__class__.__name__ or SOCK_STREAM.__eq__.__class__.__name__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra56.AF_INET.eq_class_name:
  description: "socket.AF_INET.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper' — AF_INET is an AddressFamily IntEnum instance; instance-level __eq__ is a bound method-wrapper (C slot bound to the instance); distinct from the TYPE-level wrapper_descriptor; socket_extra2/extra30 cover AF_INET.__class__.__name__.__eq__('AddressFamily') (the type of the enum member) but NOT AF_INET.__eq__.__class__.__name__; no prior socket spec checks this"
  category: type_structure
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: AF_INET.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["method-wrapper"]
  expected: true

invariant socket_extra56.SOCK_STREAM.eq_class_name:
  description: "socket.SOCK_STREAM.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper' — SOCK_STREAM is a SocketKind IntEnum instance; instance-level __eq__ is a bound method-wrapper (same pattern as AF_INET); socket_extra24/extra30/extra51 cover SOCK_STREAM class identity axes but NOT SOCK_STREAM.__eq__.__class__.__name__; no prior socket spec checks SOCK_STREAM.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method-wrapper')"
  category: type_structure
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: SOCK_STREAM.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["method-wrapper"]
  expected: true
